    <briefdescription>
<para>Non-blocking timeout helper — tick wrap-around safe. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>The &quot;has N ms elapsed?&quot; pattern is used everywhere in embedded code and is easy to get wrong with tick counter wrap-around. This header provides a tiny inline API that handles it correctly.</para>
<para>Header-only — zero code size if unused.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>Usage</title><para><programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="structSYN__Timeout" kindref="compound">SYN_Timeout</ref><sp/>to;</highlight></codeline>
